(e.g., J.I. Calzada 1457, MEXU-309621).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F85096F0847325337C2C9C053218301E" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="amphitecna megalophylla resurrected">
<paragraph id="82D346A16540043B3974A195AE92A678" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName id="528B3AB90E804AA359E5A7202F67C14C" authorityName="A. H. Gentry" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Donn. Sm." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Amphitecna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Amphitecna megalophylla" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="megalophylla">
<emphasis id="4807D5935C7AE3D80010F67D592AE9EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Amphitecna megalophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resurrected
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E61BA63DB219AD52B53EAF6AFD2FF3E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Our results indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="FCE96C6EABA8C670B968FF48769A06E8" genus="A." lsidName="A. megalophylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="megalophylla">
<emphasis id="8058EC9EA0CFC6A3D66EA581E5830B56" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. megalophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is best treated as a separate taxon that can be identified by the following features: pachycaul trees, with leaves up to 1 m long, multi-flowered inflorescences, cauliflorous and long-pedicellate flowers with a transverse fold in the corolla throat, and fruits with costate/angulate surfaces. The following species is thus treated as an accepted taxon here:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
